    </dt>
    <dd>The type of the resource. E.g. &quot;Microsoft.Compute/virtualMachines&quot; or &quot;Microsoft.Storage/storageAccounts&quot;</dd></dl>

<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#requestlogging_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">request<wbr>Logging</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type"><a href="#requestloggingresponse">Property Map</a></span>
    </dt>
    <dd>The request logging configuration for mdc, it includes advanced logging settings for all collections. It's optional.</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="rollingrate_yaml">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#rollingrate_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">rolling<wbr>Rate</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">String</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>When model data is collected to blob storage, we need to roll the data to different path to avoid logging all of them in a single blob file.
If the rolling rate is hour, all data will be collected in the blob path /yyyy/MM/dd/HH/.
If it's day, all data will be collected in blob path /yyyy/MM/dd/.
The other benefit of rolling path is that model monitoring ui is able to select a time range of data very quickly.</dd></dl>
</pulumi-choosable>
</div>
